While Kwazulu-Natal waits for national treasury to release emergency funds, The Salvation Army is calling on South Africans to extend a helping hand for families and communities affected by floods in the province. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN -  International faith-based and charity organisation, The Salvation Army is calling on South Africans to donate for KZN flood victims. This as the province await the final assessment of the extent of the damage. And the subsequent release of emergency funds from Treasury. READ: Patrice Motsepe donates R30m for flood relief The organisation's Velani Buthelezi says they asking the public to continue helping victims. The Salvation Army says those with the means to donate should contact: 028 994 4351.